Global warming is predicted to exacerbate droughts and decrease Colorado River flows, impacting water supplies for Western states.
The river is crucial for Metropolitan, Southern California's water needs, with 30% of deliveries coming from the Colorado.
Agricultural water is highlighted as a vital resource for urban use.
Uncertainty exists regarding climate change's effect on precipitation.
Seven states have agreed on drought management, as reservoir levels decline.
